cleaning text

Corpus = Corpus %>% 
  tm_map(tolower) %>% 
  tm_map(removePunctuation) %>% 
  tm_map(removeNumbers) %>% 
  tm_map(removeWords, stopwords("english"))

removeUrl = function(x)gsub("http[[:alnum:]]*", "",x)

Corpus = tm_map(Corpus,content_transformer(removeUrl))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(Corpus, content_transformer(removeUrl)):
## transformation drops documents
cleanset = tm_map(Corpus, stripWhitespace) 
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(Corpus, stripWhitespace): transformation drops
## documents
cleanset = cleanset %>% 
  tm_map(removeWords,c("aapl","apple"))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(., removeWords, c("aapl", "apple")):
## transformation drops documents
inspect(cleanset[1:5])

Term document matrix

tdm = TermDocumentMatrix(cleanset)

tdm = as.matrix(tdm)

Bar plot

W = rowSums(tdm)


selected = subset(W, W>=1)

Bar plot

barplot(
  selected,
  las = 2,
  col = rainbow(100))

Wordcloud

library(wordcloud)
## Loading required package: RColorBrewer
words = sort(rowSums(tdm),decreasing = TRUE)

set.seed(222)

  wordcloud(words = names(words),
            freq = words,
      #      max.words = 150,
            random.order = FALSE,
            min.freq = 3,
            colors = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"),
      scale = c(5,.4),
      rot.per = .29)

Interesting wordcloud

library(wordcloud2)

# best way of installing unavailable packages or loading them in current session of R
if(!require(wordcloud2)) install.packages("wordcloud2")


final = data.frame(
  names(words),words
)

final = final %>% 
  mutate(names.words.=str_replace_all(names.words.,"earnings","Birasa"))

wordcloud2(final,
           size = .7,
           shape = "star")
#ggsave(filename = "background.png",device = "png")

Letter Cloud

letterCloud(final,
            word = "A")
